Write Modes
    Controls what happens if the output path already exists.
        "overwrite" → Replace existing data
        "append" → Add to existing data
        "ignore" → Skip write if path exists
        "error" or "errorifexists" (default) → Fail if path exists



Normally when we are writing a dataframe to our target  then we have few option to control the file layout.
